  "body": "I created my svelte app by writing to command line \r\n`npm init svelte app-name ` \r\n\r\nThan I initialized Hardhat by `npx hardhat` and choosed Basic Sample Project template to get started.\r\n\r\nThan I wrote my Smart Contract and tried to deploy it to local network after I started local node by \r\n`npx hardhat node --network localhost`\r\n`npx hardhat run . \\scripts\\deploy.js`\r\n\r\nThan this error occured: \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/77447064/176016793-13edeeb5-1a58-4a8a-8d35-2946b36ca713.png)\r\n\r\nThen I tried some configuration settings, changing require statements to import statements. Changed module type. But none of them has worked. \r\nI thought maybe I got the problem so I didn't change anything at all and I used completely default setting, default contract created by Basic Sample Project. And I got same errors. So I googled it and I saw people like me on the internet have same problem with SvelteKit + Hardhat.\r\n\r\nSo I seperated my hardhat and sveltekit folders to solve this problem and as I expected It worked. But clearly there is a problem with hardhat+SvelteKit. How we can solve that problem? \r\n\r\nI saw at your website that you're hiring. I really love using Hardhat and I would want to work on that problem with SvelteKit+Hardhat (Or maybe some other problems with other web frameworks). As far as I know It works great with NextJS, ReactJS. I couldn't try it with Vue & Angular.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
